The paper analyzes the architectural features of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) and their training trajectory and generalization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The analysis includes the use of Deep Deconvolutional Networks (DC-NNs) and their effects on image space, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of nonlinearity and normalization techniques, which are common in neural networks and fall under the categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new parametrization and learning rate technique, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
